member.summary:
Retrieves the custom data of type  set at . 



Suppose we setup a new Custom Data Layer on our tilemap named "name" and we use this 
data layer to paint the name data (e.g. "floor", "wall", "lava") onto each tile.



string tileName = tileMap.GetCustomData<string>(new Vector2I(x, y), "name");

// If no data is at this tile then "" will be printed
GD.Print(tileName);

Recursively traverses a directory tree and invokes a callback for each file encountered.
The callback may control traversal flow (continue, skip directories, or stop traversal).


Traverse("res://", entry => GD.Print(entry.FullPath));

